=head1 DESCRIPTION

Details about an Network Firewall firewall.

=head1 ATTRIBUTES


=head2 DeleteProtection => Bool

Whether the firewall is protected from deletion. If set to C<true>,
then the firewall cannot be deleted.


=head2 Description => Str

A description of the firewall.


=head2 FirewallArn => Str

The ARN of the firewall.


=head2 FirewallId => Str

The identifier of the firewall.


=head2 FirewallName => Str

A descriptive name of the firewall.


=head2 FirewallPolicyArn => Str

The ARN of the firewall policy.


=head2 FirewallPolicyChangeProtection => Bool

Whether the firewall is protected from a change to the firewall policy.
If set to C<true>, you cannot associate a different policy with the
firewall.


=head2 SubnetChangeProtection => Bool

Whether the firewall is protected from a change to the subnet
associations. If set to C<true>, you cannot map different subnets to
the firewall.


=head2 SubnetMappings => ArrayRef[L<Paws::SecurityHub::AwsNetworkFirewallFirewallSubnetMappingsDetails>]

The public subnets that Network Firewall uses for the firewall. Each
subnet must belong to a different Availability Zone.


=head2 VpcId => Str

The identifier of the VPC where the firewall is used.



